<h2>Download</h2>

To install Debian GNU/Linux on a PowerMac system download the following files:<br>
<br>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/potato/main/disks-powerpc/current/powermac/linux">linux</a></li>
<li><a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/potato/main/disks-powerpc/current/powermac/images-1.44/rescue.bin">rescue.bin</a></li>
<li><a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/potato/main/disks-powerpc/current/powermac/images-1.44/driver-1.bin">driver-1.bin</a></li>
<li><a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/potato/main/disks-powerpc/current/powermac/ramdisk.image.gz">ramdisk.image.gz</a></li>
<li><a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/potato/main/disks-powerpc/base2_2.tgz">base2_2.tgz</a></li>
<li><a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/potato/main/disks-powerpc/current/powermac/BootX_1.2.2.sit">BootX</a></li>
</ul>


<p> One install report with BootX (MacOS is requred). </p>

<ol>
 <li> Installed BootX 1.1.3 in my MacOS. <p>
 <li> Put linux kernel image from disks-powerpc/current/powermac
      in "Linux Kernel" folder in my system folder. <p>
 <li> Renamed root1440.bin as "ramdisk.image.gz" and put it in
      system folder. <p>
 <li> Copied all necessary files under disks-powerpc onto external
      scsi HFS volume. <p>
 <li> Boot into linux using BootX with ramdisk check. <p>
 <li> Just followed installer with hard disk installation option
      except "Install Operating System Kernel and Modules" stage.
</ol>

<p>
 But just for mental health, I made rescue floppy under debian
 using dd and executed installation script. That's all. </p>

The BootX homepage is at: <a href="http://calvaweb.calvacom.fr/bh40"> BootX </a>
